YOLA â€“ A Senatorial aspirant under the Peoples Democratic Party PDP Hon Daniel Bwala has assured the people of Adamawa State Central Senatorial District that he would make a better representation in the Senate in 2023 to reposition the District and the entire State in general. Speaking during the flag-off of his campaign train in Gombi, Hong and Song Local Government Areas, Engr Daniel Bwala pointed out that he would provide the needed matured impetus for development to thrive in the District if the party stakeholders elect him in the forthcoming primaries.Hon Daniel Bwala who pulled a huge crowd of party faithful and supporters during the campaign told PDP members to rest assured with his candidature as he would make an excellent and mature Senator who will drive development throughout Adamawa State not only in the Central Senatorial District. He was received by large crowds of people in his Gombi Local Government Area and also in Hong and Song respectively. The PDP LGAs Chairmen in all the places he visited assured him that PDP will make the best decision in electing someone like him to represent them in the 2023 Senate. The party Chairmen thanked him for coming to indicate his preparedness to vie for the post and promised him a level playing ground to enable him to make interactions with all-party royalists at the LGAs and Ward levels so that they will understand his visions and mission. The PDP Algon chairman of Song Local Government Area, Hon Modibbo, particularly gave Hon Daniel Bwala assurances of working for him to enable him to reach out to the populace towards the primaries. Hundreds of people from other LGAs came out to cheer him as his convoys of cars moved by. The campaign train of Hon Daniel Bwala returned to Yola, the Adamawa State capital after paying courtesy calls on the various district heads of the respective Local Government Areas.